<pre><code>typedef int A;
typedef int B;

A f(A a) { return a+a; };

int main()
{
  A a = 5;
  B b = 5;
  f(a);     // I would like this to work...
  f(b);     // and this not to compile.
}
</code></pre>

<p>Now this does not work, but I know I can use a wrapper struct/class with just one member:</p>

<pre><code>class A { public: int x; A(int xx) { x = xx; }};
